Page=new Array();Page[0]=new Array("Oracle® Health Sciences Clinical One Integration Hub","Release Notes","Release 1.0","Part number: E91346-01","","216967.htm");
Page[1]=new Array("Great news for site users who work in both Clinical One and InForm for a study! Study data from Clinical One can now synchronize directly in InForm. Working in Clinical One and InForm becomes much easier, since you no longer need to answer the same question in both products.","Sponsors: How can I share my Clinical One study data to InForm studies?","All you have to do is reach out to your Oracle Sales contact! The Oracle Services team will help you define the integration points between your Clinical One and InForm studies.","Sponsors: Which InForm releases can I use with Clinical One?","See the Oracle Health Sciences Compatibility Matrix, which is available as an attachment in My Oracle Support article Oracle Health Sciences Applications Supported Technology Stack (Doc ID 180430.1).","Sponsors: How long does it take for Clinical One study data to appear in InForm?","As soon as you save a form in Clinical One, data that is mapped to InForm is available to be picked up by an integration job, which forwards them to InForm when it runs. The schedule for when this job runs is configurable. ","Sponsors: What are the configuration options?","You decide on the data that is mapped to InForm and the schedule for the integration job together with Oracle Services. For details, reach out to your Oracle Sales contact.","Send study data from Oracle Clinical One to Oracle InForm","216905.htm");
Page[2]=new Array("If you distribute your investigational product using the Almac global depot network, some steps in the lifecycle of a shipment are now automated in Clinical One. The benefits?","It's a time-saving feature for clinical supply managers and depot users.","You can see in Clinical One if the depot has received your shipment request.","Sponsors: How can I connect my Clinical One study with the Almac global depot network?","Reach out to your Oracle Sales contact if you're interested in automating the shipment workflow. The Oracle Services team will define the integration between your Clinical One study and the Almac global depot network.","Clinical supply managers and depot users: How can automation help me?","You'll see these changes in Clinical One only after the Oracle Services team sets up a study so that it is connected with the Almac global depot network. These changes don't affect site users.","See how automation can help you in the following table.","Activity in the study","Activity that is now automated in Clinical One","A new shipment is raised.","The status of the shipment changes to Processed.","The depot receives the shipment request.","The status of the shipment changes to Confirmed, a new status.","An issue occurs, such as a system outage, and the depot is unable to process the shipment request.","The status of the shipment changes to Invalid, a new status. ","Clinical supply managers: ","First, cancel the shipment so that you can set the status of the kits back to Available.","Next, do one of the following:","Allow the resupply process to create a new shipment the next time inventory runs.","Create a new manual shipment.","The depot fulfills a shipment.","The ship date is set, and the status of the shipment changes to In Transit.","Automate shipments when you distribute using the Almac global depot network","216920.htm");
Page[3]=new Array("Just reach out to your Oracle Sales representative to get started! Next, Oracle Services will identify the integration details and then configure the integration for you.","Delegated administrators: What roles do Oracle Services users need in OHSIAMS Oracle Identity Self Service? ","To set up an integration, Oracle Services users need:","The access role IntegrationHub_Production.","The access role ClinicalOne_Production.","You must set up the new Integration Hub roles so that Oracle Services team members can request access to them and so that you can approve all requests. For instructions, see the Oracle® Health Sciences Clinical One User Provisioning guide.","Clinical One administrators: What roles do Oracle Services users need in Clinical One?","Oracle Services users must have:","Oracle Services users who configure the integration need the Integration Manager global role.","The Oracle Project Manager needs the Study Creator global role.","For instructions on how to assign these roles, see the Oracle® Health Sciences Clinical One Information for Sponsor and CRO Users.","How can I get these integrations?","218687.htm");
